<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Sheriff" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Sheriff</orth> (cf. <emph>Shrieve</emph>) an officer to whom the execution of the laws in a county is entrusted: <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.3.70" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 3, 70</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.529" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 529</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.529" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 529</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.529" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 529</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.529" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 529</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.529" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 529</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.4.99" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 4, 99</bibl> (Q <emph>shrieve</emph>). <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.4.17" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 4, 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.4.17" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 4, 17</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.4.17" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 4, 17</bibl> <cit><quote>he'll stand at your door like a --'s post,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.157" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 157</bibl></cit> (at the doors of sheriffs usually posts were set up, on which proclamations were fixed).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>